            "id": "4574601",
            "title": "Orla Mining stays on track to meet FY gold production guidance",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>\n<span>Orla Mining (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ORLA\" title=\"Orla Mining Ltd.\">ORLA</a></span>) </span><span>remains on track to meet its full-year <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20471176-orla-mining-reports-first-quarter-2026-gold-production\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"consolidated gold production\">consolidated gold production</a> guidance range of 340,000–360,000 ounces, it said late on Monday, adding that </span>total gold production reached 81,206 oz, while gold sales came in slightly higher at 81,540 oz in Q1 2026.</li>\n<li>\n<span><span>\"2026 was always going to be a catalyst-rich year, and the opening months have not disappointed,\" CEO <span class=\"person\">Jason Simpson said. </span></span></span><span></span>\n</li>\n<li>During the quarter, Musselwhite mined 333,495 tonnes of ore and processed 332,822 tonnes at a mill head grade of 6.29 g/t gold. Gold recovery was 95.91%, resulting in gold production of 62,985 ounces. Musselwhite completed 3,437 meters of lateral development. 367 meters of the completed lateral development was attributed to the advance of the 1080 exploration drift. </li>\n<li>At March 31, 2026, Orla's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ORLA\" title=\"Orla Mining Ltd.\">ORLA</a>) cash and debt positions were $427.3 million and $331.3 million, respectively, resulting in a net cash position of $96.0 million.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
