            "id": "4574588",
            "title": "Goldman Sachs, Ardian acquire China Investment Corporation’s $1B US private equity stake: report",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li class=\"ArticleBodyText_articleBodyContent__17wqE typography_articleBody___5jDr\" data-component=\"paragraph\">Goldman Sachs (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GS\" title=\"The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc.\">GS</a></span>)<span> </span>and<span> </span>Ardian SAS<span> </span>were on the other side of a $1B US private equity sale by China’s sovereign wealth fund, <em>Bloomberg </em>reported citing familiar with the matter.</li>\n<li class=\"ArticleBodyText_articleBodyContent__17wqE typography_articleBody___5jDr\" data-component=\"paragraph\">The US firm’s asset management arm and the Paris-based investment firm emerged as the winning bidders late last year after state giant<span> </span>China Investment Corp.<span> </span>sought to reduce its exposure to private markets, the people said, requesting not to be named because the information is private.</li>\n<li class=\"ArticleBodyText_articleBodyContent__17wqE typography_articleBody___5jDr\" data-component=\"paragraph\">Ardian acquired the stakes at a double-digit discount, while Goldman (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GS\" title=\"The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc.\">GS</a>) did so at single digits, according to one of the people.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
